==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Isologous
<hw>I*sol"o*gous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Iso-</ets>
+ Gr. <grk>lo`gos</grk> proportion.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Having similar proportions, similar relations, or similar
differences of composition; -- said specifically of groups or series
which differ by a constant difference; <as>as, ethane, ethylene, and
acetylene, or their analogous compounds, form an <ex>isologous</ex>
series</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isomer</ent>⟦br⟧
